21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
22
23 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 12-19-102(a), concerning establishments
24 that are required to post information about the National Human Trafficking
25 Hotline, is amended to read as follows:
26 (a) The following establishments shall post in restrooms and in a
27 conspicuous place near the entrance of the establishment, or where posters
28 and notices of this type customarily are posted, a poster described in
29 subsection (b) of this section measuring at least eight and one-half inches
30 by eleven inches (8½″ x 11″) in size:
31 (1) A hotel, motel, or other establishment that has been cited
32 as a public nuisance for prostitution under § 20-27-401;
33 (2) A strip club or other sexually oriented business;
34 (3) A private club that has a liquor permit for on-premises
35 consumption and does not hold itself out to be a food service establishment;
36 (4) An airport;
